 the "SonarQube Scanner" section â€” which installs the scanner tool (CLI), not the SonarQube server configuration that Jenkins uses during withSonarQubeEnv('sonar-server').

âœ… You need to configure the SonarQube Server separately:
Hereâ€™s how to properly configure the SonarQube Server (not just the scanner):

ğŸ”§ Step-by-Step: Add SonarQube Server (sonar-server) in Jenkins
1. Go to Jenkins Dashboard
http://<your-jenkins-ip>:8080

2. Click â€œManage Jenkinsâ€
3. Go to â€œConfigure Systemâ€ (âš ï¸ Not â€œGlobal Tool Configurationâ€ this time)
4. Scroll down to the section called â€œSonarQube serversâ€
5. Click â€œAdd SonarQubeâ€
Now you'll see the â€œNameâ€ field where you can enter:
Name: sonar-server âœ… (must match your pipeline)
Server URL: http://<your-sonarqube-ip>:9000
Server Authentication Token:
Click Add â†’ Jenkins â†’ Secret text
Paste your SonarQube token (from SonarQube UI â†’ My Account â†’ Security â†’ Tokens)
